4:
Well, this is the end... We won't be
able to cover tomorrow's board if we
can't catch some fish...
10:
We heard that a big ship sunk off
the coast, and now we're dealing
with an oil spill.
12:
All that oil contaminating the water
has made it impossible for us to
catch any fish...
15:
...Hold up. That ship... Did you see it
sink?
18:
No, uh... It sunk in the middle of the
night. Happened reeeal quietly,
apparently...
21:
Then... It's possible that it wasn't an
accident.
25:
I've heard of this sort of thing before.
Nasty salvagers faking an accident
and spilling crude oil everywhere.
27:
Other ships keep away while the
salvagers pretend to clean things
up, giving them the perfect chance
to steal treasures from nearby
underwater ruins.
30:
So those jerks handle the whole act
themselves.
34:
It's not impossible to clean up a
spill... But on a scale like this...
39:
Oh, that's right! I know somebody
who can get rid of oil using alchemy!
42:
If I explain the situation, I'm sure
they'll lend a hand!
47:
Just getting rid of the crude oil won't
get us to the root of the problem,
though.
50:
That's true. We'll also have to give
those thugs a stern talking-to!
56:
Will this device be enough to clean
up the water?
60:
It's got an alchemist's seal of
approval! What could go wrong?
63:
Judging by the wind direction and
ocean currents, we must be at the
center of the spill.
68:
Hm? Is it just me, or does it sound
like something's whistling through
the air?
84:
Ah, ah... You there! Other vessel!
Leave this area immediately.
86:
We are currently recovering cargo
from a sunken vessel with
permission from the Gaean
government.
87:
Until this process is complete, entry
into this area is prohibited
90:
A sunken ship? Really? You think I'm
going to fall for that?
93:
I looked around using sonar, but
there wasn't the slightest hint of any
oil-leaking sunken freighters!
97:
You're all just after the ruins'
treasure, aren't you? SAY IT!
100:
...Ugh, what a pain in the ass. Guess
we can't let them go now!
103:
They're in a paddle steamer... The
engine room for a warship like that
would be located in...
108:
Yeah, I can take the shot at this
range!
116:
Hey! You're the ones who made the
water all icky and mucky, aren't
you? What's wrong with you?
120:
Didn't anyone ever tell you not to
litter? My hair's gonna get all sticky!
127:
Phew. I guess with the culprits all
tied up, that's one problem out of
the way.
131:
Yes! The water's getting cleaner by
the minute, too. We should be able
to prevent any further damage.
136:
By the way, what are you merfolk
doing here?
140:
Those clowns were bothering us too,
you know?
143:
So, thanks! By the way, Al and the
rest of you were cool too, but...
146:
Evelyn, was it? We were watching
you! You were all, like, BOOM! And
stuff! Now THAT'S how you get a
party started!
151: I-I'll take that as a compliment?
156:
Hey, Amelia... Have we... met
somewhere? A long time ago?
159:
A mermaid saved me from
drowning when I was a kid, you see.
164:
Huh? No way! If you were still a kid,
then I would have been small, too!
167:
It's possible that this mermaid you
speak of was Amelia's mother...
169:
Amelia looks just like her mother did
when she was younger...
175:
Wow, that's so cool! I don't suppose
you believe in fate, Amelia?
178:
Do you think you could tell me about
the time you met my mom?
182: Sure... why not? It all started when...
